<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
story for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, June 19, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   LABIZ-EXODUS (Los Angeles) _ Upon taking the city's helm seven
years ago, millionaire businessman Richard Riordan pledged to make
Los Angeles a business-friendly place. Instead, the city has
watched large corporations move their headquarters to other cities;
business tax receipts have declined in the past decade when
adjusted for inflation; nine major corporations are suing the city
alleging double taxation; and experts brand the city among the most
expensive places to do business in the region. By Alexa Haussler.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California state news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
