<P>
   VT-HEALTH-BENEFITS (Cowtown, Vt.) _ With health insurance for
nearly all children and prescription drug coverage for many people
on Medicare, Vermont is in the vanguard in terms of providing
medical benefits. The array of health benefits Vermont affords its
citizens _ not just the elderly but also children and low-income
adults _ is unmatched by any other state. And while many of
Vermont's programs would not work in larger, more urban, more
racially and ethnically diverse states, other aspects could serve
as a pattern elsewhere. Today, 93.5 percent of all Vermonters have
health insurance, including essentially all children. By contrast,
only 63 percent of low-income children in Texas and 60 percent in
Arizona are insured. What it all means, based on interviews with
the governor, doctors and ordinary folks who depend on the
benefits. By David E. Rosenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 9 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
