<HEADLINE>
SHAQ, CAN YA DIG IT?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ We were all supposta take off work today and have
a parade downtown to celebrate the Lakers' latest championship.
</P>
<P>
   Then a beautiful thing happened in Indiana-the Pacers' 33-point
win in Game 5.
</P>
<P>
   After a momentary shock, everyone put down their cell phone
around here and quickly figured it out-now they can win the whole
sha(begin ital)bang(end ital) in front of their homies.
</P>
<P>
   Which is where ``The Big Matinee Idol'' comes in-center stage at
Staples Center, to claim his prize.
</P>
<P>
   The star attraction on a team that has more movie credits per
player than championship rings has one more wrap party to
attend-bringing Hollywood's elite together one last time to see who
can close the deal on squeezin' another movie out of the league and
playoff MVP while the gettin's good.
</P>
<P>
   He's said he won't do another flick until he wins a title. That
was both a statement and a warning.
</P>
<P>
   So after tonight, accordin' to Shaq's calculations, the only
parade that'll matter is the line of couriers dropping off scripts
with agent Leonard Armato-the slick guy sitting courtside directly
across from the Lakers bench, next to Denzel ...
</P>
<P>
   -It's one thing for Rick L. Williams (Vanessa's the real fox in
that family) to try to get more airtime by pushing Pacers around.
Obviously, that ``Oz'' prison stuff must be going to his pretty
head.
</P>
<P>
   But this post-game ritual he's established with Fred ``Just
Gimme Someone To Talk To'' Roggin is downright bootlickin'. ...
</P>
<P>
   -By the way, the exit is this way, Mr. and Mrs. Rice, and thanks
for playin'. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Wanna see whether Phil Jax is brave enough to ride the parade
through d'town in a convertible with his new babe, Jeanie B., by
his side. And with her dad, Jerry B., on the other side. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Former runaway Laker Cedric Ceballos is listed among the rap
artists performing at UrbanFest L.A. this weekend on the USC
campus. Unless the family decides to take a getaway at Lake Havasu.
...
</P>
<P>
   -They'll be writing poems about Tiger Woods and country songs
about John Daly. ...
</P>
<P>
   -(begin ital)Ahhhhh Sugar(end ital) ... oh, money, money ...
</P>
<P>
   -Any more sponsor ads plastered on Oscar De La Hollywood's
trunks and he could join the Earnhardt family. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Maybe next time Laila Ali can find an 84-year-old
great-grandmother to punch out. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Classic commercial: Don Drysdale interviewing this mop-top
peewee Andre Agassi. Now, if we could just remember the product
being pushed. ...
</P>
<P>
   -Olympic-bound swimmer Lenny Krayzelburg could be more popular
than Lenny Kravitz after the upcoming Aussie Games.
</P>
<P>
   Brandweek magazine reports the Studio City dude already has
``Mary Lou Retton marketing potential,'' having supposedly locked
up $1 mil in endorsements. And Lenny did get a finance degree out
of his USC education. ...
</P>
<P>
   -And this year's Dad's Day stumper: Don't understand why Janice
Holyfield decided to end her four-year marriage with Evander.
Unless it has something to do with the fact that of the champ's
nine kids, two were born to other women since the couple exchanged
vows in '96.
</P>
<P>
   Tom Hoffarth can be reached at sptmediaaol.com or (818)
713-3661.
</P>
